cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Packet‑Rate and Size Dependent L2 Latency and Energy Measurements on a DUT
abstract: The dataset records packet‑rate and packet‑size controlled Layer‑2 latency
  tests performed with MoonGen against a device‑under‑test, capturing per‑packet latency,
  energy consumption, and process logs. Multiple experimental runs vary packet rate
  and size to evaluate throughput‑latency trade‑offs under consistent system conditions,
  including disabled CPU turbo boost and configured huge pages. Evaluation involves
  generating latency histograms and comparing energy traces across configurations,
  providing a comprehensive view of performance and power characteristics for the
  DUT.
